%N A398020 Decimal expansion of -Sum_{k>=1} lambda(k) * theta(k) * log(k) / k^2, where lambda is Liouville's function (A008836), and theta(k) is the number of unitary divisors of k (A034444).
%H A398020 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 382, Corollary 2.11.
%F A398020 Equals -Sum_{k>=1} A158522(k) * log(k) / k^2.
%F A398020 Equals (48/5)*log(A) + 96*log(A_3), where A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
%F A398020 Note that Sum_{k>=1} lambda(k) * theta(k) / k^2 = 2/5.
%e A398020 0.4050329825113293439229325474642985858842963692909017...
%t A398020 RealDigits[(48/5)*Log[Glaisher] - 96*Zeta'[-3] - 22/15, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A398020 (PARI) -(48/5)*zeta'(-1) - 96*zeta'(-3) - 2/3
%Y A398020 Cf. A008836, A034444, A073002 (Sum_{k>=1} log(k)/k^2), A074962, A158522, A243263, A398012, A398019.
